'''Payam Niazmand''' ({{langx|fa|پیام نیازمند}}; born 6 April 1995) is an Iranian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for Iranian club [[Persepolis F.C.|Persepolis]] and the [[Iran national football team|Iran national team]].<ref name="sw">{{Cite web |url=https://us.soccerway.com/players/payam-niazmand/352667/ |title=Payam Niazmand}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.tasnimnews.com/fa/news/1396/07/22/1545091/%D9%86%DB%8C%D8%A7%D8%B2%D9%85%D9%86%D8%AF-%D8%A8%D9%87-3-%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B1-%DA%A9%D9%84%DB%8C%D9%86-%D8%B4%DB%8C%D8%AA-%D9%82%D8%A7%D9%86%D8%B9-%D9%86%D9%85%DB%8C-%D8%B4%D9%88%D9%85-%D9%BE%D8%B1%D8%B3%D9%BE%D9%88%D9%84%DB%8C%D8%B3-%D9%85%D8%AF%D8%B9%DB%8C-%D8%A7%D9%88%D9%84-%D9%82%D9%87%D8%B1%D9%85%D8%A7%D9%86%DB%8C-%D8%A7%D8%B3%D8%AA |title=نیازمند: به ۳ بار کلین‌شیت قانع نمی‌شوم/ پرسپولیس مدعی اول قهرمانی است|language=Persian}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://parsfootball.com/fa/481360/%D9%BE%DB%8C%D8%A7%D9%85-%D9%86%DB%8C%D8%A7%D8%B2%D9%85%D9%86%D8%AF-5-%DA%A9%D9%84%DB%8C%D9%86-%D8%B4%DB%8C%D8%AA-8-%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B2%DB%8C/ |title=پیام نیازمند 5 کلین شیت در 8 بازی|date=30 November 2017 }}</ref>

Niazmand set the new all-time record at 940 consecutive minutes without conceding a goal. [[Mohammad Nouri (footballer)|Mohammad Nouri]] ended his goalless streak by beating him in the 50th minute of the same match.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.varzesh3.com/news/1645574/%D8%B1%DA%A9%D9%88%D8%B1%D8%AF-%D9%86%DB%8C%D8%A7%D8%B2%D9%85%D9%86%D8%AF-%D8%AA%D8%A7%D8%B1%DB%8C%D8%AE-%D8%B1%D8%A7-%D8%A7%D8%B2-%D9%86%D9%88-%D9%86%D9%88%D8%B4%D8%AA|title=تشویق با شعار پیام دست طلایی |website=www.varzesh3.com|access-date=1 November 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.irna.ir/news/83537055/پایان-۹۴۰-دقیقه-گل-نخوردن-نیازمند|title=پایان-۹۴۰-دقیقه-گل-نخوردن-نیازمند|language=Persian|trans-title=End of 940 minutes goalless for Niazmand|last=|first=|date=|website=IRNA|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> He was included in Iran's preliminary squad for the [[2019 AFC Asian Cup]].

== Club career ==
=== Paykan ===
Niazmand started his senior career in Iran at [[Paykan F.C.|Paykan]] in 2015, where he made 24 appearances in three seasons.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|date=13 July 2021|title=IR Iran's Payam Niazmand joins Portugal's Portimonense|url=https://www.the-afc.com/transfers/news/ir-iran-s-payam-niazmand-joins-portugal-s-portimonense|access-date=14 July 2021|website=the AFC|language=en-GB}}</ref>

=== Sepahan ===
In 2018, Niazmand joined [[Sepahan S.C.|Sepahan]].<ref name=":0" /> Niazmand was included in Sepahan's lineup in 89 games continuously.

=== Portimonense ===
On 13 July 2021, Niazmand joined [[Primeira Liga]] side [[Portimonense S.C.|Portimonense]].<ref name=":0" />

=== Persepolis ===
On 19 May 2025, Niazmand joined Persian Gulf Pro League side [[Persepolis F.C.|Persepolis]] on a new two-year deal.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-05-19 |title=پیام نیازمند رسما به پرسپولیس پیوست |url=https://www.isna.ir/news/1404022921195/%D9%BE%DB%8C%D8%A7%D9%85-%D9%86%DB%8C%D8%A7%D8%B2%D9%85%D9%86%D8%AF-%D8%B1%D8%B3%D9%85%D8%A7-%D8%A8%D9%87-%D9%BE%D8%B1%D8%B3%D9%BE%D9%88%D9%84%DB%8C%D8%B3-%D9%BE%DB%8C%D9%88%D8%B3%D8%AA |access-date=2025-05-20 |website=ایسنا |language=fa}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-05-19 |title=Payam Niazmand signs for Persepolis |url=https://www.tehrantimes.com/news/513262/Payam-Niazmand-signs-for-Persepolis |access-date=2025-05-20 |website=Tehran Times |language=en}}</ref>

==International career==
On 8 October 2020, Niazmand made his debut for the [[Iran national football team|Iran national team]] in a 2–1 [[Exhibition game|friendly]] win against [[Uzbekistan national football team|Uzbekistan]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=8 October 2020 |title=UZBEKISTAN VS. IRAN 1 - 2 |url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2020/10/08/world/friendlies/uzbekistan/iran/3287333/ |access-date=9 October 2020 |website=soccerway.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=8 October 2020 |title=2020 International Friendly |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/lineups?gameId=573689 |access-date=9 October 2020 |website=espn.com}}</ref>

